esertions, effect of war on country life, the progress of the war and disposition of troops.The book concludes with 261 reports from scouts from all over the country.Luke later lived at Cople and was a member of Parliament and in London during some of his governorship at Newport Pagnell.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aModern History. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / 20th Century.2bisacsh  aCivil War.  aLuke (Sir Samuel).  aNewport Pagnell.  aarmy.  acorrespondence.1 aLuke, Samuel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTibbutt, H. G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTibbutt, H. G., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781800107304?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781800107304423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781800107304/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles